---
// Solution section explaining RootSpec methodology
---

<section data-test="solution-section" class="py-16">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
    <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-12">The RootSpec Solution</h3>

    <div data-test="solution-content" class="space-y-8">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center space-x-4 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-blue-900 px-8 py-4 rounded-lg">
          <span class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">init</span>
          <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
          <span class="text-xl font-bold text-green-600 dark:text-green-400">spec</span>
          <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
          <span class="text-xl font-bold text-purple-600 dark:text-purple-400">impl</span>
          <span class="text-gray-400">→</span>
          <span class="text-xl font-bold text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400">validate</span>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mt-2">Four-step methodology for specification-driven development</p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div class="p-6 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900 rounded-lg">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300">Structured Hierarchy</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Five distinct levels from Philosophy to Fine-tuning create clear separation
            of concerns and prevent implementation details from polluting strategic decisions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900 rounded-lg">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300">Validated Implementation</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            User stories directly generate executable tests, ensuring the final product
            matches the original specification with measurable validation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900 rounded-lg">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300">Reference Constraints</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Each level can only reference certain other levels, preventing circular
            dependencies and maintaining clear information flow.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-6 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900 rounded-lg">
          <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-3 text-green-700 dark:text-green-300">Living Documentation</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            Specifications stay synchronized with implementation through automated
            testing, eliminating spec drift and documentation decay.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>